{"key":"processedPost-9825418","value":{"id":9825418,"first":9818852,"last":9825418,"when":1235061760,"utime":"02/19/09 06:42 PM","cleanedPost":"The bottom line is you can't inoculate bulk substrates with spores.&nbsp; You need to inoculate brf cakes or grains with spores, which then becomes your spawn.&nbsp; You can case your spawn and fruit it, or mix it with up to four times as much bulk substrate, in which case the spawn inoculates the bulk sub and you get a larger harvest, but a higher chance of failure.<br />I suggest using the basic <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek</a> by itself to learn the life cycle of the fungi, and then move on to other, more productive techniques as your skills improve.<br />RR"}}